00:32:13.573 --> 00:32:16.636
and it's enough to have them in
the xy, yz,

00:32:16.636 --> 00:32:18.200
and zx planes.
 

00:32:18.200 --> 00:32:20.210
So the strategy that I'm going
to follow,

00:32:20.210 --> 00:32:23.345
this is something one can skip,
but I wanted you to know the

00:32:23.345 --> 00:32:25.055
details,
if you really want to know

00:32:25.055 --> 00:32:26.308
where everything comes from.
 

00:32:26.308 --> 00:32:29.349
I'm going to write down or
search for a solution to Maxwell

00:32:29.349 --> 00:32:29.980
equations.
 

00:32:29.980 --> 00:32:32.500
I'm going to make it have a
certain form.

00:32:32.500 --> 00:32:34.818
You remember how we do this
with equations.

00:32:34.818 --> 00:32:37.579
We assume a certain form,
stick it into the equation,

00:32:37.579 --> 00:32:39.808
play with some parameters till
it works.

00:32:39.808 --> 00:32:42.638
I'm going to make it work on
infinitesimal loops and

00:32:42.638 --> 00:32:45.578
infinitesimal cubes and that's
going to be enough,

00:32:45.578 --> 00:32:47.250
because if it works on this
tiny loop,

00:32:47.250 --> 00:32:49.338
it works in a big loop,
works in a tiny cube,

00:32:49.338 --> 00:32:54.480
works on a big cube or
arbitrary surface.

00:32:54.480 --> 00:32:59.854
So let us write down the
functional form that I'm going

00:32:59.854 --> 00:33:00.750
to use.
 

00:33:00.750 --> 00:33:08.338
The functional form that I'm
going to use looks like this.

00:33:08.338 --> 00:33:12.924
I'm going to take an electric
field that is entirely in the

00:33:12.924 --> 00:33:17.273
z direction and the
z field will depend on

00:33:17.273 --> 00:33:19.328
y and t.
 

00:33:19.328 --> 00:33:22.373
And I'm going to take a
magnetic field which is going to

00:33:22.373 --> 00:33:25.804
be in the x direction and
the B field is going to

00:33:25.804 --> 00:33:29.180
depend on the y and
t. So let me tell you how my

00:33:29.180 --> 00:33:30.730
axes are defined here.
 

00:33:30.730 --> 00:33:36.190
This is x, this is
y, this is z.

00:33:36.190 --> 00:33:39.390
The electric and magnetic
fields, the electric field will

00:33:39.390 --> 00:33:41.618
always point along the z
axis.

00:33:41.618 --> 00:33:46.318
The magnetic field will always
point along the x axis.

00:33:46.318 --> 00:33:50.336
They will not vary,
as you vary x or

00:33:50.336 --> 00:33:51.390
z.
 

00:33:51.390 --> 00:33:56.750
They'll vary only if you vary
y by assumption.

00:33:56.750 --> 00:33:58.279
In general, it can vary with
everything,

00:33:58.279 --> 00:34:02.781
but I'm trying as a modest goal
to find a simple solution which

00:34:02.781 --> 00:34:07.430
has a dependence on only two of
the four possible coordinates.

00:34:07.430 --> 00:34:10.753
It depends on only y and
t, rather than x,

00:34:10.753 --> 00:34:12.130
y, z and t.
 

00:34:12.130 --> 00:34:13.880
Let's get any solution.
 

00:34:13.880 --> 00:34:15.219
We cannot get every possible
one;

00:34:15.219 --> 00:34:18.425
let's get something and
something, I assume,

00:34:18.425 --> 00:34:19.619
has this form.
 

00:34:19.619 --> 00:34:23.210
So this is called a plane wave,
because if you take the plane

00:34:23.210 --> 00:34:25.483
y = 0,
E and B are

00:34:25.483 --> 00:34:27.099
constant on that plane.
 

00:34:27.099 --> 00:34:29.226
Because when y is fixed
or some value,

00:34:29.226 --> 00:34:32.027
E and B are not
changing as you vary x

00:34:32.027 --> 00:34:32.849
and z.
 

00:34:32.849 --> 00:34:36.059
So you should think of it as
plane after plane and on each

00:34:36.059 --> 00:34:38.199
plane, the field is doing
something.

00:34:38.199 --> 00:34:39.099
It's doing the same thing.
 

00:34:39.099 --> 00:34:43.409
If I draw a plane here,
that field is a constant.

00:34:43.409 --> 00:34:45.992
E is a constant and that
plane and B is a constant

00:34:45.992 --> 00:34:46.650
on that plane.
 

00:34:46.650 --> 00:34:49.842
On another plane,
it could be a different

00:34:49.842 --> 00:34:54.949
constant, but within the plane,
it varies from plane to plane.

00:34:54.949 --> 00:34:57.860
So that is not an axiom,
that's not a law.

00:34:57.860 --> 00:35:02.550
That's an assumed simplicity in
the function I'm looking at.

00:35:02.550 --> 00:35:06.041
There's no theorem that says
that every solution to Maxwell

00:35:06.041 --> 00:35:08.268
equations much obey this
condition.

00:35:08.268 --> 00:35:10.878
In general, these functions
will be functions of x,

00:35:10.878 --> 00:35:12.059
y, z and t.
 

00:35:12.059 --> 00:35:14.420
The trick will be superposition.
 

00:35:14.420 --> 00:35:16.833
If I can get a solution that
depends only y and

00:35:16.833 --> 00:35:18.465
t,
and you can get a solution that

00:35:18.465 --> 00:35:19.690
depends on z and
t,

00:35:19.690 --> 00:35:21.829
I can add them up and they will
still be a solution,

00:35:21.829 --> 00:35:23.739
because the wave equation is
linear.

00:35:23.739 --> 00:35:24.900
You can add solutions.
 

00:35:24.900 --> 00:35:27.869
Then our sum of the two
solutions will be a function of

00:35:27.869 --> 00:35:29.190
y and z.
 

00:35:29.190 --> 00:35:30.820
You can bring in the x
and so on.

00:35:30.820 --> 00:35:34.530
So you do the simplest one,
